    "created_at": "2016-07-01T07:54:24Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-01T07:54:24Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz The `slient` attribute of the HTML5 Notification API works on macOS.\n\nhttps://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Notification/silent\n\nUsers can manually implement this with a wrapper similar to the one below\n\n``` js\nimport { remote } from 'electron';\nconst NativeNotification = window.Notification;\n\nclass SilentNotification extends NativeNotification {\n    constructor(title, opts) {\n        if (!opts.silent) {\n            opts.silent = remote.getCurrentWebContents().isAudioMuted();\n        }\n        super(title, opts);\n    }\n}\n\nwindow.Notification = SilentNotification;\n```\n"
  },
